class Solution {
    public boolean check(int[] nums) {
        int count = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            if (nums[i] > nums[(i + 1) % nums.length]) count++;
        }
        if (count > 1) return false;
        else return true;
    }
}


✅ Time Complexity

Loop runs for n elements once

Each step does O(1) work

✅ Time Complexity: O(n)

✅ Space Complexity

Only one variable count used

✅ Space Complexity: O(1)
